


Standard Input Stream Handling "istream.h"

    Macros

            The istream.h header file defines several macros
            related to stdin.

            The ISTREAM_HEIGHT macro specifies the presumed
            number of lines on the display connected to
            stdin.

            The ISTREAM_TEXT_WIDTH macro specifies the
            presumed maximum number of sequential printing
            characters that can be input via stdin.

            The ISTREAM_LOGICAL_LINE_LENGTH_MAX macro
            specifies the maximum number of characters to be
            processed between end-of-line-markers. The macro
            is intended to support imposing a limit on the
            number of characters skipped when long lines are
            encountered.

    Functions

            The istream_error function tests the error
            indicator for stdin. The istream_error function
            returns a positive value if the error indicator
            is set for stdin; otherwise, the istream_error
            function returns zero.

            The istream_eof function tests the end-of-file
            indicator for stdin. The istream_eof function
            returns a positive value if the end-of-file
            indicator is set for stdin; otherwise, the
            istream_eof function returns zero.
